The premiers of Canada'seastern provinces and the governors of America's New Englandstates urged development of Canada's offshore oil and gasfields and construction of a pipeline from Nova Scotia to NewEngland.    Newfoundland premier Brian Peckford, speaking to the annualconference of New England and eastern Canadian leaders, saiddevelopment would prevent a repetition of the energy crisis ofthe early 1970s.    The group also agreed to discuss energy and security ofsupply next spring.    Drilling off Canada's Atlantic coast has stalled sinceworld oil prices began tumbling two years ago. The resolutionsupporting a natural gas pipeline from Nova Scotia to NewEngland has been on the agenda for six years, and this is thesixth year it has been approved.    The two-day conference ends tomorrow. Reuter&#3;